## Changelog:
* Remove UseUUIDs option, UUIDs are now always used (this drops support for MC 1.7.2-1.7.4)
* Add new database connection options
* Show help if no parameter is used from console command (Fixes #50) 
* Item-Shortcut
  * No longer add the backpack item in worlds where the plugin is disabled
  * Allow items to be dropped into the backpack without opening it (drag and drop in the inventory) (thanks debarba for this great idea)
* Item-Filter
  * Add option to filter by name #33 
  * Add option to filter by lore #33
  * Add item filter whitelist mode (closes #44)
  * Blocked items can now be moved freely within the inventory while the backpack is open, just not into the backpack
* Fix bug where some list elements where lost from the config after upgrading the config file

name: v2.0
body:
## Changelog:
* More customizations
  * Every message can be changed or disabled
  * Every message sent to the client can be a JSON (this means you now can define texts for hovering and click actions)
  * Messages now have more placeholders and they are proper named to make it easier to adjust stuff
  * Every message can be sent to the client as chat message, action bar message, title, subtitle message, the send method can be configured for every single message
  * There are lots of new messages and config options
  * Every command, sub-command and flag can be translated
* Cooldowns can be synced across servers in a BungeeCord setup
* Add item filter (items that are not allowed can be filtered per material)
* Add world blacklist
* Backup and Restore functionality
  * auto backup backpacks on severe errors
* New commands
  * version
  * reload
* Technical changes
  * Switch to Java 8
  * Add an API
  * Add option to migrate database to another type
  * Use PCGF PluginLib as an optional dependency
  * Streamline naming of the plugin, config options and permissions
    * It's Minepacks everywhere now
    * All permissions are now in camelCase
    * All config options are now in PascalCase
* Drop support for Cauldron/Uranium
* Drop support for all Minecraft versions older than 1.7
